The paper discusses bibliometrics and semantic networks in the context of a geography journal, which suggests a focus on digital libraries (cs.DL) and information retrieval (cs.IR). The use of spatial analysis also suggests a potential fit with cybernetics (cs.CY) and social and information networks (cs.SI). Additionally, the paper's focus on the evolution of research areas and readership could also align with software development (cs.SD) and machine learning (cs.LG).
